entries.femaleVariant: What the--?!
OK, Got my attention.
This a prank?
All right, Songbird… Got my full attention.
Oh, very funny... This a prank? Not in the mood if so.
entries.maleVariant: Veeery funny... This a prank? Not in the mood if so.

entries.femaleVariant: Glad to hear that.
It's anything but.
But first I need you to get to that swollen appendix of Night City called Dogtown.
Dogtown? Chunk of Pacifica, exterritorial…
Lord of the land's one Kurt Hansen, international arms dealer. Corpos give it a wide berth.
I skip anything?
Nope, more or less on the button.
No-man's zone where you shoot first, ask questions later? That Dogtown?
What, the chance to live to a ripe old age not reason enough to go?
Nargh, fuckin'… argh!
Ugh, what the f-- augh! Ugh, it's like... someone shoved my head in a vise! Augh!
V... you OK? C'mon, get up.
V? You're gonna be OK.
Your nervous system took a big hit, broke down. Racing heart, cold sweat... It'll pass.
V, somethin' stinks here... Think she's… she's fuckin' with the Relic.
All true, Johnny. But don't you fret, you're both safe.
What the fuck... ?
I'm sorry.
Who the hell are you?
[Touch Songbird] You look like a construct…
Just who the hell are you, Songbird?
entries.maleVariant: Just... who the hell are you, Songbird?

entries.femaleVariant: You a construct...? Like Johnny?
[Stand] Don't know shit.
Ugh, you got... no fuckin' idea, lady...
Naaugh… ugh!
I know about the bomb tickin' in your head.
If I could disarm it now, I would in a heartbeat.
Can't know how much I'd really love to believe you, but…
Both of us on the biochip protocol at once can trigger shocks for V. Like you just saw now.
Fine. Willin' to risk it.
Dogtown's a no-go.
Puttin' it plainly – you know me, I don't know you, but I'm supposed to haul ass to Night City's worst district?
Fine. No clue what I'm steppin' into, but... no risk, no reward.
Don't go to Dogtown on a whim.
Thanks.
Uh... Thanks, I guess?
Your Relic's crowded with clusters of corrupted data. I'm dumpin' that, makin' room for stuff that'll actually be handy.
I'm not being charitable – need you at your damned best.
Dogtown's main gate – be there as soon as you can. I'll make contact again then.
[Stand] Sure hope so.
Aaghh… ugh, fuckin' hope so.
Would love to believe you.
Why should I trust you? Gave me a seizure a second ago.
How do I know I can trust you?
A side effect, I'm sorry. If it's any consolation, I will make it up to you.
Feel my fingertips tingling.
Decent soft!
Feel a… tinglin' in my fingertips. Kinda nice, actually.
entries.maleVariant: Feel a… tingling in my fingertips. Kinda nice, actually.

entries.femaleVariant: Militech firmware... Heh, my, my, solid soft!
Some preem Militech combat soft. It's just lyin' around, gatherin' dust.
Oh, it goes a lot further than tingling, trust me.
Well, a cushy government gig like mine just comes with all kinds of perks.
Better?
Try and get up.
I'm on your side, V.
We'll get along, I'm certain.
Don't wanna mess in your head more than I have to.
Construct's really done a number on you...
Take a moment, don't rush.
Are you there?
Answer, please. I know you're on the line.
Easy to disappear in Dogtown.
Dogtown... city within Night City. Know of clans who tried to establish footholds on the black market there.
Never managed to stake any claims – hell, some plain never made it back.
entries.maleVariant: Never managed to stake any claims, hell – some plain never made it back.

entries.femaleVariant: Their mistake – one you won't repeat.
Consider this a... an advance.
Now, listen. What I gave you's the skeleton soft. But the firmware's fancy, it'll learn, grow with you. It'll improve if you feed it data.
Combat analyses, logs of legendary ops, shit that'd make the NCPD piss its boots. Look around Dogtown.
Main entrance is a no-go. You don't have an entry pass, and I don't have time to produce a fake.
Lead the way.
Guess so – after you.
Such as…?
Don't make me regret this.
Ugh, better not regret this…
Leave it to me. I'll make damn sure you won't.
Gotta cut you off – for your safety, for V's safety.
V? Can you hear me?
Uh, loud and clear, whoever you are.
entries.maleVariant: Uh… uh, loud and clear, whoever you are.

entries.femaleVariant: Good. It worked.
My name is So Mi. Just... call me Songbird, though.
You must have questions. And I'll answer them in due course, shortly.
Nah, not convinced.
I'll explain everything and prove I can help you. Right now, though – I'm beggin' you, V.
Not exactly burstin' with excitement 'bout this plan.
Thank you. I appreciate this, truly.
Huh. This's one elaborate haze… or a fuckin' lifeline.
Expect you've already guessed – I'm a netrunner.
Hopped on the Relic's cognitive protocol to dial in. I see and hear what you do.
Guessin' you're a netrunner.
Startin' to put two and two together. You gotta be a netrunner – damn good one at that.
Guilty as charged.
Actually, I do.
Had to mute him for now. He hears you fine, just can't talk back.
I know, V. You've hit a dead end, nowhere to turn. Been there, believe me.
How do I help?
Plane got hacked, right? You're a 'runner – can't override?
Plane – you can't "unhack" it?
I could. All I'd need is twenty-four hours, the right setup and a bottomless pot of coffee.
None of that's available just now.
How do I help? And how much time we got?
Too little to avoid landing in Dogtown. Likely enough to minimize losses, save some folks.
That's where you come in, V.
The president's life, her safety – that's your top priority.
She'll survive the landing. Dogtown, not so sure… You'll need to get 'er out of the plane before anyone else does.
How in the--
Understand how serious this is?
You're all we've got, V.
Nothing's free, including my help.
Mentioned you could help me.
Man's got a thousand-and-one reasons to want Myers as a hostage.
Tellin' me the NUS president, Rosalind Myers, is there with you?
You really with the president?
Sitting right across from me.
She knows the situation. Waitin' for your "yes."
Nothin's for free, Songbird. We should talk biz.
Said you could help me. That the plain truth?
"Anyone else"? Specifically? Meanin', you expectin' company?
entries.maleVariant: "Anyone else"? Specifically? Meanin' you expectin' company?

entries.femaleVariant: Kurt Hansen, Dogtown's commander-in-chief.
Expectin' any company at the landing site?
He couldn't've netjacked the plane on his own. Meaning Washington's got a mole problem.
Can we count on you?
So – with me?
This is some heavy shit.
Heavy shit. 'M I really your one contact?
You're my last and only hope.
That one'll need solvin' later.
Just now, I'm on board Space Force One. Sitting right across from Rosalind Myers, president of the New United States of America.
The president? Fuck. I, uh... No, y-you're not joking.
entries.maleVariant: The president? Fuck. Hah, I... No, you're not jokin'.

entries.femaleVariant: The plane's been hacked, trajectory's set for Night City. They'll bring us down in Dogtown soon.
Right now… You're our one contact on the ground.
Our comms are down, most likely jammed. The Relic was my only option.
I know who you are – know your situation, your… problem.
And I can save your life.
Breathe deep, count to ten, recite a mantra…
Whatever brings calm, helps you stabilize.
You'll feel better, any second now…
Gotta get there first.
I'll be right beside you – as much as I can.
[Stand] The hell you doin' to me?!
The fff... fuck you doin'? This a trap?
entries.maleVariant: The fu... the fuck you doin'? This a trap?

entries.femaleVariant: Exact opposite. It's a helping hand.
Wait by Dogtown's main gate. I'll get in touch again there.
I can cure you. Once and for all.
Just got a taste of my abilities, I believe. There's more.
No, V. I'm a netrunner.
You'll slip in "the back way," quiet as you can. We really don't need anyone spotting you, scanning you.
Dead serious, yes.
Nah, fuck off!
Riiiiight.
Aaaahh!
